{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":850,"text":"So, has everybody heard of CRISPR?"},{"time":3883,"text":"I would be shocked if you hadn't."}]},{"cues":[{"time":6509,"text":"This is a technology --\nit's for genome editing --"},{"time":9735,"text":"and it's so versatile and so controversial"},{"time":12593,"text":"that it's sparking all sorts\nof really interesting conversations."},{"time":16631,"text":"Should we bring back the woolly mammoth?"},{"time":19281,"text":"Should we edit a human embryo?"},{"time":22041,"text":"And my personal favorite:"},{"time":24997,"text":"How can we justify\nwiping out an entire species"},{"time":28672,"text":"that we consider harmful to humans"},{"time":31140,"text":"off the face of the Earth,"},{"time":32466,"text":"using this technology?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":35165,"text":"This type of science\nis moving much faster"},{"time":38472,"text":"than the regulatory mechanisms\nthat govern it."},{"time":41340,"text":"And so, for the past six years,"},{"time":43431,"text":"I've made it my personal mission"},{"time":45863,"text":"to make sure that as many people\nas possible understand"},{"time":48897,"text":"these types of technologies\nand their implications."}]},{"cues":[{"time":52021,"text":"Now, CRISPR has been the subject\nof a huge media hype,"},{"time":57089,"text":"and the words that are used most often\nare \"easy\" and \"cheap.\""},{"time":62337,"text":"So what I want to do is drill down\na little bit deeper"},{"time":65500,"text":"and look into some of the myths\nand the realities around CRISPR."}]},{"cues":[{"time":70954,"text":"If you're trying to CRISPR a genome,"},{"time":73594,"text":"the first thing that you have to do\nis damage the DNA."},{"time":77098,"text":"The damage comes in the form\nof a double-strand break"},{"time":80164,"text":"through the double helix."},{"time":81752,"text":"And then the cellular repair\nprocesses kick in,"},{"time":85088,"text":"and then we convince\nthose repair processes"},{"time":87751,"text":"to make the edit that we want,"},{"time":90054,"text":"and not a natural edit."},{"time":91620,"text":"That's how it works."},{"time":93929,"text":"It's a two-part system."},{"time":95676,"text":"You've got a Cas9 protein\nand something called a guide RNA."},{"time":99071,"text":"I like to think of it as a guided missile."},{"time":101557,"text":"So the Cas9 --\nI love to anthropomorphize --"},{"time":104227,"text":"so the Cas9 is kind of this Pac-Man thing"},{"time":107481,"text":"that wants to chew DNA,"},{"time":109050,"text":"and the guide RNA is the leash\nthat's keeping it out of the genome"},{"time":113230,"text":"until it finds the exact spot\nwhere it matches."},{"time":116912,"text":"And the combination of those two\nis called CRISPR."},{"time":119830,"text":"It's a system that we stole"},{"time":121422,"text":"from an ancient, ancient\nbacterial immune system."}]},{"cues":[{"time":125469,"text":"The part that's amazing about it\nis that the guide RNA,"},{"time":130041,"text":"only 20 letters of it,"},{"time":131956,"text":"are what target the system."},{"time":134570,"text":"This is really easy to design,"},{"time":136737,"text":"and it's really cheap to buy."},{"time":138985,"text":"So that's the part\nthat is modular in the system;"},{"time":143014,"text":"everything else stays the same."},{"time":145481,"text":"This makes it a remarkably easy\nand powerful system to use."}]},{"cues":[{"time":150047,"text":"The guide RNA and the Cas9\nprotein complex together"},{"time":154311,"text":"go bouncing along the genome,"},{"time":156267,"text":"and when they find a spot\nwhere the guide RNA matches,"},{"time":159784,"text":"then it inserts between the two strands\nof the double helix,"},{"time":162663,"text":"it rips them apart,"},{"time":164692,"text":"that triggers the Cas9 protein to cut,"},{"time":167962,"text":"and all of a sudden,"},{"time":169816,"text":"you've got a cell that's in total panic"},{"time":171740,"text":"because now it's got a piece\nof DNA that's broken."}]},{"cues":[{"time":175000,"text":"What does it do?"},{"time":176320,"text":"It calls its first responders."},{"time":178959,"text":"There are two major repair pathways."},{"time":181605,"text":"The first just takes the DNA\nand shoves the two pieces back together."},{"time":186698,"text":"This isn't a very efficient system,"},{"time":188820,"text":"because what happens is\nsometimes a base drops out"},{"time":191573,"text":"or a base is added."},{"time":193024,"text":"It's an OK way to maybe, like,\nknock out a gene,"},{"time":196841,"text":"but it's not the way that we really want\nto do genome editing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":200098,"text":"The second repair pathway\nis a lot more interesting."},{"time":203017,"text":"In this repair pathway,"},{"time":204677,"text":"it takes a homologous piece of DNA."},{"time":207382,"text":"And now mind you, in a diploid\norganism like people,"},{"time":210046,"text":"we've got one copy of our genome\nfrom our mom and one from our dad,"},{"time":214318,"text":"so if one gets damaged,"},{"time":215617,"text":"it can use the other\nchromosome to repair it."},{"time":218036,"text":"So that's where this comes from."},{"time":220518,"text":"The repair is made,"},{"time":222006,"text":"and now the genome is safe again."}]},{"cues":[{"time":224616,"text":"The way that we can hijack this"},{"time":226497,"text":"is we can feed it a false piece of DNA,"},{"time":230229,"text":"a piece that has homology on both ends"},{"time":232397,"text":"but is different in the middle."},{"time":234120,"text":"So now, you can put\nwhatever you want in the center"},{"time":236611,"text":"and the cell gets fooled."},{"time":238150,"text":"So you can change a letter,"},{"time":240293,"text":"you can take letters out,"},{"time":241582,"text":"but most importantly,\nyou can stuff new DNA in,"},{"time":244530,"text":"kind of like a Trojan horse."}]},{"cues":[{"time":247089,"text":"CRISPR is going to be amazing,"},{"time":249298,"text":"in terms of the number of different\nscientific advances"},{"time":252940,"text":"that it's going to catalyze."},{"time":254621,"text":"The thing that's special about it\nis this modular targeting system."},{"time":257866,"text":"I mean, we've been shoving DNA\ninto organisms for years, right?"},{"time":261657,"text":"But because of the modular\ntargeting system,"},{"time":263808,"text":"we can actually put it\nexactly where we want it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":267423,"text":"The thing is that there's\na lot of talk about it being cheap"},{"time":273116,"text":"and it being easy."},{"time":274882,"text":"And I run a community lab."},{"time":278242,"text":"I'm starting to get emails from people\nthat say stuff like,"}]},{"cues":[{"time":281822,"text":"\"Hey, can I come to your open night"},{"time":284243,"text":"and, like, maybe use CRISPR\nand engineer my genome?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":287884,"text":"(Laugher)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":289018,"text":"Like, seriously."}]},{"cues":[{"time":291376,"text":"I'm, \"No, you can't.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":293203,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":294237,"text":"\"But I've heard it's cheap.\nI've heard it's easy.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":296616,"text":"We're going to explore that a little bit."},{"time":298823,"text":"So, how cheap is it?"},{"time":300796,"text":"Yeah, it is cheap in comparison."},{"time":303665,"text":"It's going to take the cost of the average\nmaterials for an experiment"},{"time":307308,"text":"from thousands of dollars\nto hundreds of dollars,"},{"time":309864,"text":"and it cuts the time a lot, too."},{"time":311824,"text":"It can cut it from weeks to days."},{"time":314246,"text":"That's great."},{"time":315762,"text":"You still need a professional lab\nto do the work in;"},{"time":318476,"text":"you're not going to do anything meaningful\noutside of a professional lab."},{"time":322012,"text":"I mean, don't listen to anyone who says"},{"time":324040,"text":"you can do this sort of stuff\non your kitchen table."},{"time":327421,"text":"It's really not easy\nto do this kind of work."},{"time":331953,"text":"Not to mention,\nthere's a patent battle going on,"},{"time":334285,"text":"so even if you do invent something,"},{"time":336135,"text":"the Broad Institute and UC Berkeley\nare in this incredible patent battle."},{"time":342795,"text":"It's really fascinating\nto watch it happen,"},{"time":345207,"text":"because they're accusing each other\nof fraudulent claims"},{"time":348479,"text":"and then they've got people saying,"},{"time":350234,"text":"\"Oh, well, I signed\nmy notebook here or there.\""},{"time":353042,"text":"This isn't going to be settled for years."},{"time":355167,"text":"And when it is,"},{"time":356351,"text":"you can bet you're going to pay someone\na really hefty licensing fee"},{"time":359660,"text":"in order to use this stuff."},{"time":361343,"text":"So, is it really cheap?"},{"time":363148,"text":"Well, it's cheap if you're doing\nbasic research and you've got a lab."}]},{"cues":[{"time":369220,"text":"How about easy?\nLet's look at that claim."},{"time":372417,"text":"The devil is always in the details."},{"time":375881,"text":"We don't really know\nthat much about cells."},{"time":379036,"text":"They're still kind of black boxes."},{"time":380730,"text":"For example, we don't know\nwhy some guide RNAs work really well"},{"time":385614,"text":"and some guide RNAs don't."},{"time":387701,"text":"We don't know why some cells\nwant to do one repair pathway"},{"time":391193,"text":"and some cells would rather do the other."}]},{"cues":[{"time":394270,"text":"And besides that,"},{"time":395578,"text":"there's the whole problem\nof getting the system into the cell"},{"time":398471,"text":"in the first place."},{"time":399759,"text":"In a petri dish, that's not that hard,"},{"time":401785,"text":"but if you're trying to do it\non a whole organism,"},{"time":404254,"text":"it gets really tricky."},{"time":406224,"text":"It's OK if you use something\nlike blood or bone marrow --"},{"time":409434,"text":"those are the targets\nof a lot of research now."}]},{"cues":[{"time":411685,"text":"There was a great story\nof some little girl"},{"time":413960,"text":"who they saved from leukemia"},{"time":415636,"text":"by taking the blood out, editing it,\nand putting it back"},{"time":418334,"text":"with a precursor of CRISPR."},{"time":420869,"text":"And this is a line of research\nthat people are going to do."},{"time":423689,"text":"But right now, if you want to get\ninto the whole body,"},{"time":426266,"text":"you're probably going\nto have to use a virus."},{"time":428434,"text":"So you take the virus,\nyou put the CRISPR into it,"},{"time":430831,"text":"you let the virus infect the cell."},{"time":432561,"text":"But now you've got this virus in there,"},{"time":434728,"text":"and we don't know what the long-term\neffects of that are."},{"time":437440,"text":"Plus, CRISPR has some off-target effects,"},{"time":439732,"text":"a very small percentage,\nbut they're still there."},{"time":442717,"text":"What's going to happen\nover time with that?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":446039,"text":"These are not trivial questions,"},{"time":448275,"text":"and there are scientists\nthat are trying to solve them,"},{"time":450939,"text":"and they will eventually,\nhopefully, be solved."},{"time":453249,"text":"But it ain't plug-and-play,\nnot by a long shot."},{"time":456907,"text":"So: Is it really easy?"},{"time":459032,"text":"Well, if you spend a few years\nworking it out in your particular system,"},{"time":463389,"text":"yes, it is."}]},{"cues":[{"time":465426,"text":"Now the other thing is,"},{"time":467534,"text":"we don't really know that much about how\nto make a particular thing happen"},{"time":473917,"text":"by changing particular spots\nin the genome."},{"time":477306,"text":"We're a long way away from figuring out"},{"time":479497,"text":"how to give a pig wings, for example."},{"time":482364,"text":"Or even an extra leg -- I'd settle\nfor an extra leg."},{"time":485252,"text":"That would be kind of cool, right?"},{"time":486922,"text":"But what is happening"},{"time":488482,"text":"is that CRISPR is being used\nby thousands and thousands of scientists"},{"time":492856,"text":"to do really, really important work,"},{"time":495252,"text":"like making better models\nof diseases in animals, for example,"},{"time":500720,"text":"or for taking pathways\nthat produce valuable chemicals"},{"time":505726,"text":"and getting them into industrial\nproduction in fermentation vats,"},{"time":510021,"text":"or even doing really basic research\non what genes do."}]},{"cues":[{"time":514022,"text":"This is the story of CRISPR\nwe should be telling,"},{"time":516975,"text":"and I don't like it\nthat the flashier aspects of it"},{"time":520463,"text":"are drowning all of this out."},{"time":522243,"text":"Lots of scientists did a lot of work\nto make CRISPR happen,"},{"time":526841,"text":"and what's interesting to me"},{"time":528484,"text":"is that these scientists\nare being supported by our society."}]},{"cues":[{"time":533423,"text":"Think about it."},{"time":534606,"text":"We've got an infrastructure that allows\na certain percentage of people"},{"time":538983,"text":"to spend all their time doing research."},{"time":542984,"text":"That makes us all the inventors of CRISPR,"},{"time":546998,"text":"and I would say that makes us all\nthe shepherds of CRISPR."},{"time":551490,"text":"We all have a responsibility."}]},{"cues":[{"time":553749,"text":"So I would urge you to really learn\nabout these types of technologies,"},{"time":558010,"text":"because, really, only in that way"},{"time":560415,"text":"are we going to be able to guide\nthe development of these technologies,"},{"time":564791,"text":"the use of these technologies"},{"time":566747,"text":"and make sure that, in the end,\nit's a positive outcome --"},{"time":571034,"text":"for both the planet and for us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":574698,"text":"Thanks."}]},{"cues":[{"time":575914,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}